abstract: Mr. Bennet, a senator from Colorado, may be best known for helping negotiate a comprehensive immigration proposal in 2013.
snippet: Mr. Bennet, a senator from Colorado, may be best known for helping negotiate a comprehensive immigration proposal in 2013.
lead_paragraph: Senator Michael Bennet of Colorado may be best known for being part of the so-called Gang of Eight: four Democratic and four Republican senators who negotiated a comprehensive immigration proposal in 2013.

abstract: New York Times reporters followed the exchanges and provided context around the candidates’ claims.

lead_paragraph: Ten candidates vying for the 2020 Democratic presidential nomination took the stage on Thursday in Miami for the second of back-to-back debate nights. The 10 other candidates who qualified for the debates appeared on the same stage on Wednesday.

headline_main: Analysis of Night 2 of the June Democratic Debates

abstract: Kamala Harris stood out from the 10-person crowd several times during the NBC debate. Her exchange with Joe Biden, who is leading in the polls, put him on the defensive.

abstract: Mr. Bennet, a senator from Colorado, has called for a lifetime ban on members of Congress becoming lobbyists, and other measures meant to reboot American democracy.
snippet: Mr. Bennet, a senator from Colorado, has called for a lifetime ban on members of Congress becoming lobbyists, and other measures meant to reboot American democracy.
lead_paragraph: Senator Michael Bennet of Colorado, 54, is participating in the Democratic primary’s second debate on Thursday in Miami. He is a moderate who gained national attention after delivering a passionate speech on the Senate floor during a government shutdown.

abstract: The company will give world premieres of ballets by Twyla Tharp and Gemma Bond, and the New York premiere of a Jessica Lang work.
snippet: The company will give world premieres of ballets by Twyla Tharp and Gemma Bond, and the New York premiere of a Jessica Lang work.
lead_paragraph: American Ballet Theater’s Women’s Movement — a recent initiative to support female choreographers, who have often struggled to get their dances staged by major companies — will yield more fruit this fall, when the company will present world premieres of ballets by Twyla Tharp and Gemma Bond and the New York premiere of a Jessica Lang work.

abstract: The new generation of desirable models includes specimens most serious collectors wouldn’t have sniffed at a few years ago.
snippet: The new generation of desirable models includes specimens most serious collectors wouldn’t have sniffed at a few years ago.
lead_paragraph: When Kurt Glaubitz bought a vintage British automobile, it wasn’t for its sweeping curves or coach-built looks. Despite its scrawny-necked snorkel (for fording rivers) and boxy lines, however, his 1992 Land Rover Defender fits right into the latest wave of cars being scooped up by a new generation of collectors.

abstract: Elizabeth Warren, Bernie Sanders, Kamala Harris and other candidates finally take notice.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren, Bernie Sanders, Kamala Harris and other candidates finally take notice.
lead_paragraph: Child care is not something nice to have. It is a pressing crisis holding back the entire economy. Growth depends on more people working and working more productively. When parents who want to work can’t fully participate, America hurts only itself. Fortunately, many of the people running for president appear to have gotten the memo, making child care likely to be a topic during the Democratic debates.
